OL,3,CLeicester City Council confirms Diwali
OL,4,Ccelebrations to be scaled back
OL,6,FCllr Manjula Sood, Assistant City
OL,7,FMayor responsible for Community
OL,8,FCohesion, said: "Looking forwards we
OL,9,Fwant to involve more people,
OL,10,Fespecially young people and volunteers
OL,11,F` who give so much time every year `
OL,12,Fin the development of our Diwali Day
OL,13,Fprogramme.
OL,15,F"We also want to work closely with the
OL,16,Fwealth of South Asian arts
OL,17,Forganisations and businesses we have
OL,18,Fin Leicester to help us to grow and
OL,19,Ffind other sources of funding for this
OL,20,Fimportant celebration."
